Conservation and Recreation Lands in Iowa

descript.purpose: This digital, geographically referenced data set was developed by the Iowa Department of Natural Resources to carry out agency responsibilities related to management, protection, and development of Iowa's natural resources.
descript.abstract: This dataset represents conservation and recreation lands in the state of Iowa. Boundaries of areas represent differences in ownership and managing agency of the area. The sources of this data is derived from many different sources, mainly from the agency responsible for the area. Some of these conservation areas are under private ownership and public access is not allowed, signs and private property should be respected.
descript.supplinf: This dataset is not intended to represent survey-quality boundaries. Signage, or fencing on the ground should be respected as the area boundary.

procstep.procdesc: The processes used to create this file consist of merging, dissolving, splitting, cleaning, exploding and snapping polygons together.

attracc.attraccr: The attributes from the differing source material have been lumped and split according to type, management, and owner. The attributes are considered to be as accurate as possible. If errors are noticed, changes will be made promptly.

dataqual.logic: Polygons have all been closed, and slivers have been eliminated in a majority of the coverage. Geometry has been checked and corrected.
dataqual.complete: Lands not yet in this file would be most land under City control. They will be added as time permits. Also, County CCB areas will be updated in the future with new acquisitions.
